Someone posted the other day about how he hallucinated for an hour or so after eating London's spiciest curry at a restaurant specialized in unusually spicy foods. Good example on the Dr. Pavlov principle of how substances have different effects at different doses using Capsicin.

E.g. Caffeine in small amounts is a sedative, in moderate amounts is a stimulant, and in giant amounts is a hallucinogen (apparently like capsacin). Maybe everything is actually a hallucinogen in giant amounts. Food for thought.
